ModelHeader.Author: Conant_Wolfe
ModelHeader.ModelTitle: YeastGlyco: WGD param and added PDH

note.value: Model used by Conant and Wolfe, 2007, unpublished. Taken from Pritchard and Kell, 2002, Eur J Biochem 269: 3894-3904.
-Made all rate laws dependent on the product of WGD_E and Vmax
-Added a new compartment of unit volume to represent the mitochondria
-Added two new fixed products AcCoA and Co2 as the outputs of PDH
-Added a mass-balance reaction for the transport of Pyr into the new compartment
-Added a PDH reaction using the kinetic values described in Rizzi et al., 1997, Biotechnology and Bioengineering 55: 592-608
Results for the analysis in the above manuscript (Figure 2C) were obtained by manually changing the value of [WGD] to range between 0.65 and 1.0.
